
Overview of verb hop

The verb hop has 6 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                            
1. (7) hop, skip, hop-skip -- (jump lightly)
2. (1) hop -- (move quickly from one place to another)
3. (1) hop -- (travel by means of an aircraft, bus, etc.; "She hopped a train to Chicago"; "He hopped rides all over the country")
4. hop -- (traverse as if by a short airplane trip; "Hop the Pacific Ocean")
5. hop -- (jump across; "He hopped the bush")
6. hop -- (make a jump forward or upward)
